results.wikipedia_summary: Two species of chough /ˈtʃʌf/ constitute the genus Pyrrhocorax of the Corvidae (crow) family of birds. These are the Red-billed Chough (Pyrrhocorax pyrrhocorax), and the Alpine or Yellow-billed Chough (P. graculus). The White-winged Chough of Australia, despite its name, is a member of the family Corcoracidae and only distantly related.
